========================================================
FCFS - First Come First Served
========================================================
Non-preemptive. Among available processes, run the earliest arriving process first. Ties use input order.

Execution timeline:
  [ 0,  8)  P1
  [ 8, 12)  P2
  [12, 21)  P3
  [21, 26)  P4
  [26, 28)  P5

Compact Gantt view:
  |0 P1 |8 P2 |12 P3 |21 P4 |26 P5 |28

Per-process results:
Process        Arr   Burst    Prio  Deadline  FirstStart    Finish   Waiting  Turnaround  Response   Missed
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
P1               0       8       2        18           0         8         0           8         0       no
P2               1       4       1        10           8        12         7          11         7      yes
P3               2       9       3        25          12        21        10          19        10       no
P4               3       5       2        16          21        26        18          23        18      yes
P5               6       2       1        12          26        28        20          22        20      yes

Summary metrics:
  Makespan              : 28
  Total busy time       : 28
  CPU utilization       : 100.00%
  Throughput            : 0.18 processes/unit-time
  Average waiting time  : 11.00
  Average turnaround    : 16.60
  Average response time : 11.00
  Deadline misses       : 3 / 5


========================================================
SJF - Shortest Job First
========================================================
Non-preemptive. Whenever the CPU becomes free, run the available process with the smallest burst time.

Execution timeline:
  [ 0,  8)  P1
  [ 8, 10)  P5
  [10, 14)  P2
  [14, 19)  P4
  [19, 28)  P3

