========================================================
Round Robin
========================================================
Preemptive. Each ready process gets at most quantum=3 time units per turn. Arrivals at a time-slice boundary are queued before the preempted process.

Execution timeline:
  [ 0,  3)  P1
  [ 3,  6)  P2
  [ 6,  9)  P3
  [ 9, 12)  P4
  [12, 15)  P1
  [15, 17)  P5
  [17, 18)  P2
  [18, 21)  P3
  [21, 23)  P4
  [23, 25)  P1
  [25, 28)  P3

Compact Gantt view:
  |0 P1 |3 P2 |6 P3 |9 P4 |12 P1 |15 P5 |17 P2 |18 P3 |21 P4 |23 P1 |25 P3 |28

Per-process results:
Process        Arr   Burst    Prio  Deadline  FirstStart    Finish   Waiting  Turnaround  Response   Missed
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
P1               0       8       2        18           0        25        17          25         0      yes
P2               1       4       1        10           3        18        13          17         2      yes
P3               2       9       3        25           6        28        17          26         4      yes
P4               3       5       2        16           9        23        15          20         6      yes
P5               6       2       1        12          15        17         9          11         9      yes

Summary metrics:
  Makespan              : 28
  Total busy time       : 28
  CPU utilization       : 100.00%
  Throughput            : 0.18 processes/unit-time
  Average waiting time  : 14.20
  Average turnaround    : 19.80
  Average response time : 4.20
  Deadline misses       : 5 / 5


==================== POLICY COMPARISON ====================
Policy                              Avg Wait  Avg Turnaround      Avg Resp    Misses      Util %
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
FCFS - First Come First Served         11.00           16.60         11.00         3      100.00
SJF - Shortest Job First                7.80           13.40          7.80         3      100.00
Priority Scheduling                     8.20           13.80          8.20         4      100.00
Round Robin                            14.20           19.80          4.20         5      100.00

Interpretation hints:
  - Lower waiting/turnaround time is usually better for batch-style workloads.
  - Lower response time is important for interactive workloads.
  - Round Robin often improves response time, but can increase turnaround time.
  - Deadline misses show whether a policy is suitable for time-bound workloads.
